    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but every time i test drive it i get this really annoying high-pitched squealing sound coming from the front left side. not sure if i messed something up or if it's just a bad sensor or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal after a brake job on a Camry is often a sign of something getting a bit too loose, or maybe a piece of grime is catching on something. You should first check the brake caliper and the pads themselves, as those are the most likely culprits. If you don't find anything obvious, it might be a sensor, but don't worry too much about that yet; a loose bolt is usually the first thing to look for.",
      "source": "target",
