    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the bolts and they seem tight. the squeal is constant when i'm moving, not just when i hit the brakes. could it be a stuck caliper or something else making that sharp noise?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A constant squeal while moving, not just when braking, suggests something is rubbing continuously, which could indeed be a stuck caliper or perhaps the pad isn't seating correctly. You should inspect the caliper slide pins, which are the bolts that allow the caliper to slide freely on the mounting bracket. If those pins are seized or dirty, the caliper might be binding against the rotor even when you're driving.",
      "source": "target",
